results.name: Denominator of Sum(k^mu(k): 1<=k<=n), where mu is the Moebius function (A008683).
comment: a(n) is a divisor of A034386(n), the product of the primes <= n. Does a(n) = A034386(n) for infinitely many n?
program: (PARI) a(n) = denominator(sum(k = 1, n, k^moebius(k))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Aug 29 2013
xref: Numerators are in A080306. Cf. A080304, A080305, A034386.
